<P><HI>Sea&s;onable Advice</HI> CONCERNING THE <HI>TAVERN.</HI></P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="title page">
<PB REF="002780_0002_0FE632AD449026E0" MS="y">
<P>A <HI>Serious Addre&s;s</HI> To tho&s;e Who unnece&s;&s;arily frequent THE TAVERN, AND Often &s;pend the Evening IN <HI>Publick Hou&s;es.</HI></P>
<P>By &s;everal MINISTERS.</P>
<P>To which is added, A private Letter on the Subject, by the late Rev. Dr. <HI>increa&s;e Mather.</HI></P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Luk. 14.35.</HI></BIBL>
<P>He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.</P></Q>
<P><HI>BOSTON,</HI> N E. Printed for <HI>S Gerri&s;h,</HI> at the lower end of Cornhill. 1726.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="preface">
<PB REF="002780_0003_0FE6325CA7B1F4F0">
<HEAD>The Preface.</HEAD>
<P>IT is matter of &s;orrowful, Ob&s;ervation, That <HI>New-England's</HI> primitive Ways are not now &s;een among us in their former Glory and Beauty; but we have too &s;adly <HI>left our fir&s;t Love</HI>: and Cu&s;toms, of ill fame, very in|con&s;i&s;tent with that Profe&s;&s;ion we make of the pure&s;t Reformation, are vi&s;ibly &s;preading in the mid&s;t of us.</P>
<P>IN particular, it is for a Lamentation, that many Per&s;ons do unnece&s;&s;arily frequent <HI>Taverns</HI> and <HI>Publick Hou&s;es</HI>; even to a Scan|dal, and to the manife&s;t Prejudice and Hin|drance of all Godline&s;s and Hone&s;ty.</P>
<P><PB N="ii" REF="002780_0004_0FE6325CAB1E1DD0">WE do therefore hold our &s;elves oblig'd, in faithfulne&s;s to our great Lord &amp; Ma&s;ter, the Credit of the Go&s;pel, and the Welfare of precious Souls, to joyn in the following <HI>Serious Addre&s;s</HI> to our Neighbours. Which, &s;ome of us having had the Compo&s;ing, and others the Peru&s;al of, we all concur to the Scope &amp; Sub&s;tance; as apprehending it to be a &s;ea&s;onable and needful Te&s;timony: And do earne&s;tly (in the Meekne&s;s of <HI>CHRIST,</HI> and yet with his Authority) exhort all into who&s;e hands it may come, <HI>Tho&s;e</HI> particularly who are under our more immediate In&s;pection and Charge, (for who&s;e Souls we would watch as they that mu&s;t give Account; that we may do it with Joy, and not with Grief; for that is unprofitable for them) to take what is here offer'd, into their mo&s;t &s;erious Con&s;ideration, and to &s;ubmit their Con&s;ci|ences unto the Mind and Will of GOD, as it is herein pre&s;ented to them.</P>
<P>THE Addre&s;s is made in this mo&s;t publick manner; Partly becau&s;e if there be any &s;o <HI>&s;ecret</HI> in their practice of the Evil witne&s;s'd again&s;t, as to e&s;cape our Notice and per&s;onal Applications, we hope this Admonition by the way of the <HI>Pre&s;s,</HI> may find them out: Partly al&s;o that tho&s;e upon whom a tran&s;ient oral Di&s;cour&s;e is apt to make but little Im|pre&s;&s;ion, may by having a <HI>printed</HI> one in their
<PB N="iii" REF="002780_0005_0FE6325DAFFE2DB8">
hands, have opportunity more <HI>deliberately</HI> to weigh our Advice: And partly that we might in this way <HI>reach</HI> tho&s;e whom we can't &s;peak to from the <HI>Pulpit.</HI></P>
<P>THIS Admonition is primarily intended for <HI>Chri&s;tian Profe&s;&s;ors,</HI> of whom we wou'd hope that &s;ome are among the Faithful in CHRIST; who will be di&s;po&s;ed to &s;ay with the Royal P&s;almi&s;t, <HI>Let the Righteous &s;mite me, it &s;hall be a Kindne&s;s</HI> &mdash;. And as Brethren, we wou'd re&s;tore &s;uch in the &s;pirit of <HI>meekne&s;s,</HI> con&s;idering our &s;elves as Men &s;ubject to like pa&s;&s;ions with others. Yet it mu&s;t be ob&s;erv'd, that in the cour&s;e of this Addre&s;s, here and there are mingled &s;ome oc|ca&s;ional Hints, more e&s;pecially pointed at the gro&s;ly <HI>Scandalous,</HI> who de&s;erve to be <HI>&s;harply rebuked,</HI> and often have been.</P>
<P>WE wou'd not be under&s;tood to involve all that are faulty, in one common Charge of Guilt, without di&s;tinction: or to impute every ill property and effect of the Tavern-meetings, in the &s;ame degree, to every one. Nor is it de&s;ign'd to ca&s;t <HI>Reproach</HI> on any par|ticular Per&s;ons; but We &s;incerely aim (by the Grace of GOD) at the Reforming of &s;uch as are fallen into &s;o unhappy a Practice, and the Warning of others who are like to be in|&s;nared.</P>
<P><PB N="iv" REF="002780_0006_0FE6325DB3704A08">WE be&s;eech all concern'd, &s;olemnly to examine them&s;elves, to ponder the path of their feet, and prove their own ways; and make particular application of the Reproofs and Warnings here given, as an inform'd Con&s;cience &s;hall direct: Awfully remembring this matter will quickly be judg'd according to the Go&s;pel, at the enlighten'd Tribunal of CHRIST, <HI>Who&s;e We are, and whom we &s;erve.</HI></P>
